<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-10T01:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-10T01:29:00-05:00" n="604" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/412</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-10T01:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1917, 1 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your April 7, 6 p.m. Railroad repaired to Omaja, trains running to Las
                            Tunas ten miles west. Permanent military guard now stationed American
                            settlement. Another detachment entering district ordered to clear
                            surrounding country of rebels or robbers.</p>
                        <p>Have received a letter from Omaja. People suffered theft of horses and
                            supplies. One youth reported whipped by rebels. Has been most isolated
                            place Cuba and totally unprotected account destruction railroad bridges
                            for hundred miles east and west.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>